title = "Health Inspection Readiness & Daily Walkthrough"

content = """
- Perform a daily 10-point walkthrough before the first service. Use a checklist on a tablet. Points: 1) Handwash sinks – soap, paper towels, hot water. 2) Sanitizer buckets – 200-400 ppm quat or 50-100 ppm chlorine. 3) Food temperatures – cold items <41°F, hot items >135°F. 4) Date labels – all prepared items labeled with date and contents. 5) Storage – raw meat below ready-to-eat, no cross-contamination. 6) Pest control – no droppings, traps in place. 7) Cleaning logs – dish machine temp log, hood cleaning log. 8) Employee health – no sick staff working. 9) Allergen procedures – separate utensils for allergens. 10) Waste management – dumpster area clean, lids closed.
- Correct any violation immediately. If a critical violation (e.g., cold food above 41°F) is found, discard the product, retrain the responsible employee, and document the corrective action.
- Keep a binder with all health inspection reports, food safety certificates, and cleaning schedules. Update the binder monthly.
- Train all staff on the 10-point checklist during onboarding and quarterly refreshers. Conduct a mock health inspection every 3 months.
"""  # noqa: E501

version = "0.0.1"
